race.comment: PHAROAH'S DAUGHTER (7) registered a strong win at Kilmore two runs ago. Not disgraced last time out when prominent at the bend before finishing second over 1600m at Ballarat, beaten 1.3 lengths. Has the class to figure prominently. THINXZO (3) was safely held when fourth last time out over 1400m at Warrnambool, beaten 4 lengths. That followed a win at this track at the previous outing. Perfectly placed and is sure to play a pivotal role. BRISEIS ECLIPSE (9) started this prep with a win two runs ago. Not disgraced last time out when fifth over 1100m at Horsham, beaten 2 lengths after she did her best work late. SMOKE 'N' OAKUM (6) value at odds.
